<div id="review_373219930" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/373219930" />
    <a title="Dagny" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10742602-dagny"><img alt="Dagny" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1341610852p2/10742602.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/373219930?book_show_action=true">Jul 20, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dagny" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dagny" href="/user/show/10742602-dagny">Dagny</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10742602-dagny?shelf=peters-ellis">peters-ellis</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer373219930" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13567774805783164609">In the Sixth Chronicle of Brother Cadfael, The Virgin in the Ice, it is the winter of 1139. This chronicle is one of the first ones I read and still a favorite. Three refugees of the feud between Maud and Stephen are missing. While Brother Cadfael is on another mission, he discovers clues to the fate of the missing travellers. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


