<div id="review_2816974213" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2816974213" />
    <a title="Marta" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2168708-marta"><img alt="Marta" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1271458432p2/2168708.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2816974213?book_show_action=true">May 12, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Marta" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Marta" href="/user/show/2168708-marta">Marta</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/39338911-the-virgin-in-the-ice">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2168708-marta?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2168708-marta?shelf=mystery-thriller">mystery-thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2168708-marta?shelf=audio">audio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2168708-marta?shelf=library">library</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2816974213" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8472678241934068596">I seem to have gotten hooked on brother Cadfael. I am starting to see the formula: people in need stumble into Cadfael’s path, he takes care of them; something bad happens, someone gets murdered, and Cadfael uses his forensic skills and logic to figure it out. There is always a young couple that falls in love, or perhaps two, and there is always an obstacle that Cadfael helps them overcome, whike musing over his own bygone days when he was young and in love. He looks on youth as an age of innoce</span>
  <span id="freeText8472678241934068596" style="display:none">I seem to have gotten hooked on brother Cadfael. I am starting to see the formula: people in need stumble into Cadfael’s path, he takes care of them; something bad happens, someone gets murdered, and Cadfael uses his forensic skills and logic to figure it out. There is always a young couple that falls in love, or perhaps two, and there is always an obstacle that Cadfael helps them overcome, whike musing over his own bygone days when he was young and in love. He looks on youth as an age of innocence and rash mistakes. And there is the historical backdrop of medieval civil war.<br /><br />This installlment is quite dark, as it involves raping, pillaging and mass murder by bandits. But all comes to good end as our young couple gets together, and we get an unusally (even for Peters) cheesy bit at the end. Yes, this is cheesier fare than my usual, especially the innocent lovers bits, but I enjoy the characters, the monastic life, and there is a good variety of the mysteries so far.<br /><br />I am listening and the availability of the audiobooks is out of order, but it does not seem to matter, as each story is independent.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8472678241934068596" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


