<span id="freeTextContainer3552424048431972341">This is so great. I had read it twice at least, I&apos;m ashamed how little I remembered. There is a lot of action, villainous villains, brave heroes, beautiful girls, a mountain stronghold and a serious battle ... and Cadfael&apos;s &quot;nunc dimittis&quot; moment - sorry, spoiler ahead! - when he realises he has a son! A marvellous creature, too. We&apos;ll see more of him, we must. Yes, I loved this. :)</span>
  <span id="freeText3552424048431972341" style="display:none">This is so great. I had read it twice at least, I'm ashamed how little I remembered. There is a lot of action, villainous villains, brave heroes, beautiful girls, a mountain stronghold and a serious battle ... and Cadfael's "nunc dimittis" moment - sorry, spoiler ahead! - when he realises he has a son! A marvellous creature, too. We'll see more of him, we must. Yes, I loved this. :)</span>
